  "title": "Light Trapping in Photonic Crystal Thin-Film Solar Cells",
  "description": "Cross-section showing how a 3D photonic crystal structure enhances absorption in a thin-film solar cell. Shows incoming light, the photonic crystal diffraction layer, guided resonant modes, and the absorption enhancement vs wavelength plot comparing planar vs PC structures. Illustrates the key physics: diffraction of incident light into guided modes, increased optical path length, and absorption beyond the Lambertian limit.",
